author: David Hinojosa, Staff Writer
title: Alvarado, Hageman race to District 27-6A titles
text:
Alvarado, Hageman race to District 27-6A titles Stevens star is No. 1; Holmes’ Hageman, too By David Hinojosa Published 6:04 pm, Saturday, October 17, 2015 
Elizabeth Alvarado didn’t mess with implementing a complicated game plan for Saturday morning’s District 27-6A championships. 
Instead, the Stevens junior relied on her natural talent and newly found confidence to carry her to her first district title. 
Alvarado covered the 5,000-meter course at Brandeis High School in 19 minutes, 1.34 seconds. She led from the opening gun and held off Warren’s Hunter Paul (19:05.21) and Brandeis’ Chelsea Smith (19:12.17) for the title. 
For more, visit ExpressNews.com.
